Stir tomatoes, kidney beans, black beans, corn, vegetable broth, carrots, celery, onion, chili powder, and garlic together in a large saucepan. Place a cover on the pan and bring the mixture to a boil. Reduce heat to low and cook chili-soup at a simmer until the vegetables are tender, about 30 minutes. Ladle chili-soup into 4 bowls; top each portion with 1/4 cup Mexican cheese blend and 1 tablespoon sour cream.